    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if automation and aging are also huge factors, why does it seem like the conversation always comes back to the safety net being the \"major driver\"? it feels like a lot of people use that argument to push for cutting benefits even when the data on things like automation is just as strong. don't you think that focus might be a bit one-sided?",
